# GoalifyNow E2E Testing Rules

## Overview
End-to-end testing rules for the GoalifyNow application using Playwright with TypeScript.

---

## Test Structure & Organization

### Directory Structure
```
tests/
├── config/               # Test configuration and environment files
│   ├── environments/     # Environment-specific configs (local, staging, production)
│   └── test-config.ts    # Centralized configuration
├── fixtures/             # Test data and fixtures
├── helpers/              # Utility functions for tests
├── pages/                # Page Object Model (POM) classes
├── setup/                # Global setup and fixtures
│   ├── global-setup.ts   # Runs before all tests
│   ├── global-teardown.ts# Runs after all tests
│   └── test-fixtures.ts  # Custom Playwright fixtures
├── specs/                # Test specifications organized by feature
│   ├── smoke/            # Critical path tests (@smoke)
│   ├── auth/             # Authentication tests
│   ├── properties/       # Property management tests
│   ├── finances/         # Financial tests
│   ├── documents/        # Document management tests
│   └── ...               # Other feature tests
└── utils/                # Shared utilities
    ├── auth-helper.ts    # Authentication helpers
    ├── api-helper.ts     # API testing utilities
    └── test-data-manager.ts # Test data lifecycle management
```

### Test Tagging Strategy
**ALWAYS** tag tests appropriately for selective execution:

| Tag | Purpose | When to Run |
|-----|---------|-------------|
| `@smoke` | Critical path tests | Every deployment, PR |
| `@critical` | Must-pass tests | Before any release |
| `@regression` | Full test coverage | Nightly/weekly |
| `@prod` | Safe for production | Can run in prod env |
| `@api` | API-only tests | CI pipelines |
| `@e2e` | Full user journey | Integration testing |

```typescript
// Example with multiple tags
test('Critical login flow @smoke @critical @prod', async ({ page }) => {
  // Test implementation
});
```

