## Page Object Model (POM) Pattern

### Creating Page Objects
**ALWAYS** extend `BasePage` for consistent functionality:

```typescript
import { Page } from '@playwright/test';
import { BasePage } from './base-page';
import TestConfig from '../config/test-config';

export class MyFeaturePage extends BasePage {
  // Use data-testid selectors - they're stable and purpose-built
  private readonly submitButton = '[data-testid="submit-button"]';
  private readonly errorMessage = '[data-testid="error-message"]';
  
  constructor(page: Page) {
    super(page);
  }

  async goto(): Promise<void> {
    await this.page.goto('/my-feature');
    await this.waitForPageLoad();
  }

  async submitForm(): Promise<void> {
    await this.clickElement(this.submitButton);
    await this.waitForLoadingComplete();
  }
}
```

### Selector Priority
1. **`data-testid`** attributes (preferred - stable and purpose-built)
2. **Semantic HTML** (`button`, `input`, `a`)
3. **ARIA attributes** (`role`, `aria-label`)
4. **Text content** (for user-facing labels)
5. **CSS classes** (avoid - fragile)

