## Test Data Management

### Using Dedicated E2E Users
E2E tests MUST use dedicated E2E users seeded for SeedPackType.E2E:

```typescript
import TestConfig from '../config/test-config';

const landlordUser = TestConfig.credentials.landlord;
const tenantUser = TestConfig.credentials.tenant;
const adminUser = TestConfig.credentials.admin;
```

Defaults: `e2e-landlord@demo.com`, `e2e-tenant@demo.com`, `e2e-admin@demo.com` (password: `Test123!`).

**Strict guard:** Config fails fast if `TEST_*_EMAIL` env vars use legacy aliases (`landlord1@demo.com`, `tenant1@demo.com`, `admin@rentifynow.com`, etc.) unless `E2E_ALLOW_LEGACY_DEMO_USERS=true`.

### Test Data Lifecycle (AAA Pattern)
```typescript
test('should create and delete test data', async ({ page, testDataManager }) => {
  // ARRANGE - Create test data
  const testProperty = await testDataManager.createTestProperty(authenticatedUser.token, {
    title: `E2E Test Property ${Date.now()}`
  });
  
  // ACT - Perform test actions
  await page.goto(`/properties/${testProperty.id}`);
  
  // ASSERT - Verify results
  await expect(page.locator('h1')).toContainText(testProperty.name);
  
  // CLEANUP - Automatic via testDataManager fixture
});
```

