## Authentication Patterns

### Using Test Fixtures
```typescript
// Import from custom fixtures
import { test, expect } from '../../setup/test-fixtures';

test.describe('Authenticated Feature', () => {
  test('should access dashboard @smoke', async ({ page, demoUsersAvailable }) => {
    // Skip if demo users not seeded
    test.skip(!demoUsersAvailable, 'Demo users not seeded');
    
    // Test with authenticated session from fixture
    await page.goto('/dashboard');
  });
});
```

### Manual Login When Needed
```typescript
import { AuthHelper } from '../utils/auth-helper';

test('specific auth test', async ({ page }) => {
  const authHelper = new AuthHelper(page);
  
  // Login via API (faster, handles rate limiting)
  await authHelper.loginViaAPI({
    email: TestConfig.credentials.landlord.email,
    password: TestConfig.credentials.landlord.password
  });
});
```

