## Best Practices

### DO ✅
- Use `data-testid` attributes for element selection
- Wait for network idle before assertions
- Handle rate limiting with retry logic
- Use meaningful test names that describe the scenario
- Group related tests with `test.describe()`
- Tag tests appropriately for CI/CD filtering
- Clean up test data after tests
- Handle cookie consent banners
- Use `force: true` for clicks blocked by overlays (sparingly)

### DON'T ❌
- Hard-code timeouts (use `TestConfig.timeouts`)
- Use CSS selectors that depend on styling
- Create tests that depend on other tests' state
- Skip error handling in page objects
- Use `test.only` in committed code
- Rely on fixed delays (`page.waitForTimeout`)
- Create duplicate user accounts in tests

